</p>
<h1>Power Pepper Recovery</h1>
<p class="note">A nutrient-rich, <span class="highlight">anti-inflammatory powerhouse</span> smoothie for post-hike revival.</p>
<h2 class="section-title">Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>100g frozen mixed peppers</li>
<li>1 frozen banana</li>
<li>75g frozen mango or pineapple</li>
<li>1 cube frozen spinach</li>
<li>200ml cooled nettle tea</li>
<li>1 tsp hemp protein powder</li>
<li>½ tsp cinnamon</li>
<li>1 tsp cacao powder</li>
<li><em>Optional:</em> 1 medjool date (if you want more sweetness)</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="section-title">Instructions</h2>
<ul>
<li>Brew nettle tea and allow it to cool completely.</li>
<li>Combine all ingredients in your NutriBullet or high-speed blender.</li>
<li>Blend on high for 60 seconds until smooth and creamy.</li>
<li>Taste and adjust sweetness by adding the date if needed.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="section-title">Nutritional Highlights</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Calories:</strong> ~180 kcal</li>
<li><strong>Protein:</strong> 5g</li>
<li><strong>Carbohydrates:</strong> 32g</li>
<li><strong>Fat:</strong> 2.5g</li>
<li><strong>Micros:</strong> Vitamin C, Iron, Magnesium, Potassium, Beta-Carotene</li>
<li><strong>Actions:</strong> Antioxidant, Anti-inflammatory, Muscle Recovery</li>
</ul>
